</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Midwifery is a vital part of healthcare, providing essential care and support during pregnancy, childbirth, and the postnatal period. The Royal College of Midwives, as the professional body for midwifery, is instrumental in maintaining high standards within the profession. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into the RCM's role, its impact on midwifery practice, and the best practices recommended for compliance with legislative and regulatory frameworks. </span>
</p></div></div></div></div></div><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Previous" class="pf-slider-prev none hide"></button><button type="button" style="visibility:visible" aria-label="Next" class="pf-slider-next none hide"></button></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-3609" data-category="Collection Suggestion" data-name="Tea" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-kYHfwS doYKjf pf-16_ pf-color-scheme-1"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-hAcGzb cVhebe"><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-17_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-18_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-19_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key facts and statistics</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-21_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-22_ pf-text-1"><strong>Membership</strong> - The RCM has over 48,000 members, including midwives, maternity support workers, and student midwives.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1"><strong>Training and education</strong> - The RCM provides extensive training resources and continuing professional development opportunities to ensure midwives are up-to-date with the latest practices and guidelines.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1"><strong>Advocacy</strong> - The RCM actively campaigns for better maternity services and supports policies that benefit mothers, babies, and families.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Quality of care</strong> - According to the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE), high-quality midwifery care can significantly improve maternal and neonatal outcomes.













</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-30_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-31_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-32_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Midwifery</strong> - The health profession that deals with pregnancy, childbirth, and the postpartum period, including care of the newborn.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>RCM</strong> - The Royal College of Midwives, a professional organisation dedicated to the development and support of midwives and the midwifery profession.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>NMC</strong> - The Nursing and Midwifery Council, which regulates nurses and midwives in the UK to ensure high standards of practice.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-41_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-42_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-43_ pf-heading-1-h3">The RCM’s role and impact
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Professional development and education</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-47_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The RCM is pivotal in providing midwives with educational resources and professional development opportunities. It offers a range of courses and workshops covering various aspects of midwifery, from clinical skills to leadership training. These resources help midwives stay current with best practices and innovations in maternity care.














</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-49_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Advocacy and representation</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-51_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The RCM represents the interests of midwives at national and international levels. They advocate for policies that improve maternity services and ensure that midwives' voices are heard in policy-making processes. This advocacy is crucial in shaping a healthcare environment that supports both midwives and the families they care for.















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-53_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Standards and guidelines</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-55_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The RCM collaborates with regulatory bodies like the NMC to develop and uphold standards for midwifery practice. They provide guidelines and best practice recommendations that help midwives deliver safe, effective, and compassionate care. These standards are essential for maintaining public trust in midwifery services.
















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-57_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-58_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for compliance
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-61_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Adherence to legislation and regulations</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-63_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Midwives must comply with various legislative and regulatory requirements to ensure the safety and well-being of mothers and babies. Key regulations include:















</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-65_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-66_ pf-text-1"><strong>Health and Safety at Work Act 1974</strong> - Ensures a safe working environment for midwives.&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-68_ pf-text-1"><strong>Equality Act 2010</strong> - Protects against discrimination in the workplace.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-70_ pf-text-1"><strong>NMC code of conduct </strong>- Sets out the professional standards that nurses and midwives must uphold.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-72_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Continuous Professional Development (CPD)</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-74_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">CPD is critical for maintaining and enhancing midwifery skills and knowledge. The RCM offers numerous CPD opportunities, which are crucial for compliance with NMC revalidation requirements. Regular training ensures that midwives are equipped to provide high-quality care and meet the latest clinical standards.
















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-76_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Utilisation of technology</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-78_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Embracing technology, such as electronic health records and compliance management software like ComplyPlus™, can streamline administrative tasks and ensure adherence to regulations. These tools help midwives manage their workload efficiently and maintain accurate records, which is vital for both patient safety and legal compliance.

















</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-80_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-81_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-82_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommendations
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-84_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-85_ pf-text-1"><strong>Engage with RCM resources</strong> - Midwives should actively utilise the training and resources provided by the RCM to stay informed and competent.



</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-87_ pf-text-1"><strong>Implement best practices</strong> - Follow the RCM's guidelines and standards to ensure high-quality care and compliance with regulatory requirements.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-89_ pf-text-1"><strong>Leverage technology</strong> - Use tools like ComplyPlus™ to manage compliance and regulatory requirements efficiently.















</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-91_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-92_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-93_ pf-heading-1-h3">Conclusion
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-95_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(74, 144, 226);"></span>The Royal College of Midwives is a vital institution in the UK healthcare system, ensuring that midwives are well-trained, supported, and equipped to deliver exceptional care. By adhering to the guidelines and standards set by the RCM and embracing modern technology, midwives can ensure they provide the best possible care while meeting all legislative and regulatory requirements.




